  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add sliced leeks and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly caramelized, about 20 minutes.",
    "Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add smoked paprika, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add red wine vinegar and water, and bring to a boil.",
    "Cover the pot and transfer to the oven, where it will braise for 25-30 minutes, or until the leeks are very tender.",
    "Remove from the oven and serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley or thyme, if desired."
